</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Wid.</SPEAKER>
<P>It was impo&s;&s;ible to be ill with him, he was of &s;o excellent a temper: but this makes my ca&s;e perfectly in&s;tructing to others, and proves effectually, that no good|ne&s;s of the di&s;po&s;ition, no exce&s;s of affection, no prudent compliances, though they make the ca&s;e rather better than wor&s;e, can yet make it up, no, not in the lea&s;t, or any way balance the inexpre&s;&s;ible deficiency that &s;uch a breach in religious matters makes in a family.</P>
